---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="About LibGuides" description="Learn about our LibGuides platform and how it can help with your research.">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <header class="mb-8">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">About LibGuides</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600">
        Our mission is to provide high-quality research guides and educational resources to support academic success.
      </p>
    </header>
    
    <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <h2>What are LibGuides?</h2>
        <p>
          LibGuides are curated research guides created by librarians to help students, faculty, and researchers 
          navigate the complex world of research and information resources. These guides are designed to provide 
          targeted help for specific subjects, courses, or research topics.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          Each guide contains carefully selected resources, tips for effective research, and contact information 
          for librarians who can provide additional assistance. Our LibGuides platform is constantly evolving to 
          meet the changing needs of our academic community.
        </p>
        
        <h2>How to Use LibGuides</h2>
        <p>
          LibGuides can be used in various ways depending on your research needs:
        </p>
        
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Starting a research project:</strong> Find recommended databases, books, and journals for your topic.</li>
          <li><strong>Course-specific research:</strong> Look for guides tailored to your course requirements.</li>
          <li><strong>Citation help:</strong> Learn how to properly cite sources in different formats.</li>
          <li><strong>Research methods:</strong> Discover strategies for effective research in your field.</li>
          <li><strong>Data management:</strong> Find resources for organizing and managing research data.</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2>Our Team</h2>
        <p>
          Our LibGuides are created and maintained by a team of experienced librarians with expertise in various 
          disciplines. Each librarian brings specialized knowledge in their subject areas and is committed to 
          helping users find the information they need.
        </p>
        
        <p>
          Librarians regularly update guides to ensure they contain the most current and relevant resources. 
          They are also available for consultations to provide more personalized assistance with your research.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section id="contact" class="bg-primary-50 rounded-lg shadow-md p-8 mb-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-primary-800 mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
      
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-8">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-600 mb-3">Library Information</h3>
          <address class="not-italic text-gray-700">
            <p class="mb-2">University Library</p>
            <p class="mb-2">1000 Campus Drive</p>
            <p class="mb-2">Anytown, ST 12345</p>
            <p class="mb-2">
              <strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:library@example.edu" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-800">library@example.edu</a>
            </p>
            <p>
              <strong>Phone:</strong> <a href="tel:+15551234567" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-800">(555) 123-4567</a>
            </p>
          </address>
          
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-600 mt-6 mb-3">Hours</h3>
          <div class="grid grid-cols-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
            <div class="py-2 border-b border-gray-200">Monday - Thursday</div>
            <div class="py-2 border-b border-gray-200">8:00 AM - 10:00 PM</div>
            
            <div class="py-2 border-b border-gray-200">Friday</div>
            <div class="py-2 border-b border-gray-200">8:00 AM - 8:00 PM</div>
            
            <div class="py-2 border-b border-gray-200">Saturday</div>
            <div class="py-2 border-b border-gray-200">10:00 AM - 6:00 PM</div>
            
            <div class="py-2 border-b border-gray-200">Sunday</div>
            <div class="py-2 border-b border-gray-200">12:00 PM - 8:00 PM</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-600 mb-3">Send Us a Message</h3>
          <form class="space-y-4">
            <div>
              <label for="name" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Name</label>
              <input 
                type="text" 
                id="name" 
                name="name" 
                class="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-500 focus:border-primary-500"
                required
              />
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <label for="email" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Email</label>
              <input 
                type="email" 
                id="email" 
                name="email" 
                class="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-500 focus:border-primary-500"
                required
              />
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <label for="subject" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Subject</label>
              <input 
                type="text" 
                id="subject" 
                name="subject" 
                class="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-500 focus:border-primary-500"
                required
              />
            </div>
            
            <div>
              <label for="message" class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700 mb-1">Message</label>
              <textarea 
                id="message" 
                name="message" 
                rows="4" 
                class="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-primary-500 focus:border-primary-500"
                required
              ></textarea>
            </div>
            
            <button 
              type="submit" 
              class="bg-primary-600 hover:bg-primary-700 text-white font-medium py-2 px-4 rounded-md transition-colors"
            >
              Send Message
            </button>
          </form>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="bg-white rounded-lg shadow-md p-8">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">How do I request a new guide?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            If you would like to request a new LibGuide for a specific subject or course, please contact the library's 
            reference desk or email us at <a href="mailto:library@example.edu" class="text-primary-600 hover:text-primary-800">library@example.edu</a>. 
            We'll connect you with the appropriate subject librarian.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">How often are guides updated?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            LibGuides are reviewed and updated regularly to ensure they contain the most current and relevant resources. 
            The date of the last update is displayed on each guide. If you notice outdated information, please let us know.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Can I suggest resources for a guide?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Yes! We welcome suggestions for resources to include in our guides. Please contact the librarian listed on 
            the guide with your recommendations.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">How do I access subscription databases from off-campus?</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            Most library resources can be accessed from off-campus using your university login credentials. When you click 
            on a database link, you'll be prompted to sign in with your university ID and password.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </div>
</Layout>